subject: OS-7601 want channel support for imgadm
commitMessage: OS-7601 want channel support for imgadm

comments.message:
Patch Set 1: CI-Testing+1

"make check" passed ok

Patch Set 1:

I'm not convinced this is really ready yet, but
I'm posting these bits really to get suggestions
on the correct approach on maintaining ./src/img
in smartos-live.

In particular, the *imgadm* changes themselves are,
I think, ready for review, but I'm not so sure about
the massive churn in the node_modules directory.

I spent a while trying to get the 
src/img/tools/update-node-modules.sh script working,
but am not sure to what extent we want to further
manually prune the dependencies we're pulling in here.

I'm going to be on PTO for two weeks on Monday, and
wanted to get my changes posted somewhere people could
see them.

I believe the tests will all pass at this point
(but want to do a test run on a Jenkins build just to be
certain)

Abandoned

Abandoning this wad in favor of using a much lighter-weight backport of channel support to current sdc-client bits
